### Alternating Grid & High-Sensitivity Overhaul đźš€

Following explicit Awwwards-style architectural guidelines:
*   **50:50 Side-by-Side Flexbox:** Completely removed vertical model stacking. [page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/app/page.tsx) now enforces `md:flex-row` and `md:flex-row-reverse` alternating layouts across **every** section.
*   **Exact Model Mapping:** Rebuilt the [Canvases.tsx](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Canvases.tsx) wrappers so specific models sit perfectly adjacent to their relevant glassmorphism cards (e.g., *Gunung Gila* gets [great_mountain.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/great_mountain.glb), *Skills* gets [rotating_circle.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/rotating_circle.glb), *Hobbies* gets [chess_set.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/chess_set.glb)).
*   **Hyper-Reactive 3D Modifiers:** Multiplied the `useFrame` pointer delta by `5x` making the liquid metal models aggressively spin and warp based on minimal interaction. 
*   **Vivid Lighting & Framing:** Replaced all variable lighting setups with a universal stark setup: `<ambientLight intensity={2.5} />`, an intense `<directionalLight position={[5, 10, 5]} intensity={3} />`, and exact `<PerspectiveCamera position={[0, 0, 8]} fov={45} />` to tightly frame the models within their half-screen columns.

**Status:** The dark molten 3D portfolio is functionally complete, visually refined, and structurally sound. Server runs successfully on `http://localhost:3000`.

### Awwwards Caliber Refinements đźŚź

Following the extreme structural guidelines of award-winning platforms:
*   **The Drop Entrance (Zero-Lag Strict Defer):** Injected a lean HTML/CSS `<Preloader />` React component wrapped in `AnimatePresence`. The entire exit sequence perfectly executes a `[0.76, 0, 0.24, 1]` cubic bezier. Crucially, the 3D `<Canvas>` chunks are all **strictly deferred** via `next/dynamic` (`ssr: false`) and a `show3D` React state flag fired exactly inside Framer's `onAnimationComplete`, entirely eliminating early WebGL compile stutter.
*   **Immersive Molten Background:** Nuked the plain black background and injected a massive `[150, 150]` `<Plane>` rendering a custom GLSL `onBeforeCompile` Simplex Perlin Noise vertex shader hooked to a base `MeshPhysicalMaterial`. The z-depth translates and recalculates normals smoothly utilizing `useThree((state) => state.pointer)` to distort waves cleanly around the user's cursor.
*   **Studio WebGL Lighting & Great Mountain:** Built an authentic 3-point Studio Lighting setup within [GlobalLights](file:///C:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Scene.tsx#155-178) using powerful Spotlights (Key), warm Directional (Fill), and Rim Backlighting. Injected a dedicated high-intensity spotlight plus `margin={1.0}` `<Bounds>` exclusively for the *Great Mountain* module ensuring instant, high-contrast visibility against the OLED drop.
*   **Elegant Card Proportions & Auras:** Minimized the 3D Bounding Wrappers to `md:w-2/5` and `max-h-[350px]`, simultaneously giving the primary Text Cards dominant real estate at `md:w-3/5`. Encapsulated the `<Canvas>` containers inside specialized relative `bg-white/5` glass boxes backed by a deep `blur-3xl` Cyan/Purple radial gradient aura.
*   **Idle Breathing vs Action Spin:** Reduced native `useEffect/useFrame` rotational delta to merely `0.1x` (creating a very slow "breathing" effect). Fast, liquid-distorting multipliers of `5.0x` are injected *only* when the pointer is locally within the bounds of a specific Canvas bounding box.

### The Master Polish (Final Touches) âś¨
*   ***Putih Kilat* Silver Shimmer:** Completely rewrote the global Interactive Background to utilize `@react-three/drei`'s `<MeshDistortMaterial>` bound to an enormous Sphere mesh (`[15, 128, 128]`). Enforced an ultra-glossy `clearcoat=1.0` material that reflects highly specialized `<pointLight>`s mapping exactly to the user's cursor dynamically (`state.pointer`), creating an immersive sliding silver sheen wherever the mouse goes. Added floating [.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/chess_set.glb) particles via [cc0_-_drops.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/cc0_-_drops.glb).
*   **3D Dark Chrome Polishing:** Removed aggressive `MeshDistortMaterial` noisy shader vertex modifications from all standalone GLB objects. Restricted objects purely to an ultra-sleek `MeshPhysicalMaterial` set strictly to `color: #0a0a0a, metalness: 0.8, roughness: 0.2, clearcoat: 0.5`. This massively improves recognition and legibility of the models.
*   **Zero Duplication 1:1 Engine Architecture:** Hardcoded explicit references for exactly 10 user-provided [.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/chess_set.glb) assets into 10 unique Canvases across [Scene.tsx](file:///C:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Scene.tsx). No single model ever renders twice, enforcing true visual storytelling per section.
*   **Tailwind ESM Native Migration:** Re-configured [tailwind.config.js](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/tailwind.config.js) with correct `export default` module definition, preventing Next.js 16/Turbopack CommonJS compilation mismatch execution halts.
*   **Pristine Hero Architecture:** Formatted the opening section exclusively into `grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2`, absolutely segregating text into Left Col and anchoring the rounded profile photo into Right Col. Dropped the 3D `<HeroCanvas/>` securely into the negative space.
*   **Card Background Optimization:** Stripped duplicate `glass` blur filtering across the site by restricting backdrop configurations entirely onto the `<GlassCard>` atoms rather than rendering boxes within global [AlternatingRow](file:///C:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/app/page.tsx#56-72) boxes.
*   **Massive Footer Overhaul & Magnetic CTA:** Built a custom `<MagneticButton>` leveraging `framer-motion` `[spring]` interpolations that subtly pull contact buttons towards the mouse. Re-engineered the footer entirely out of standard layout gridsâ€”infusing a massive `backdrop-blur-3xl` glass container over a huge custom scale `[2, 2, 2]` [FooterCanvas](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Canvases.tsx#143-154) representing the *Castle On Hills* suspended over a custom `blur-[100px]` dynamic emission core.
### Bug Fixes & Precision Tuning đź› 
*   **Raycaster Touch & Scroll Adjustments:** Fixed the global offset of `useCursor` and interactive elements by assigning `style={{ touchAction: 'none' }}` globally and locking the `eventSource` precisely to `document.body` across all 10 dynamically loaded `<Canvas>` components.
*   **Camera Clipping (Z-Fighting):** Expanded the `<PerspectiveCamera>` rendering constraints (added `near={0.1} far={2000}`) within [IntiMobilityScene](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Scene.tsx#530-553) and [ProjectScene](file:///C:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Scene.tsx#384-409) to ensure the extremely large bounding boxes do not abruptly disappear from the frustration frustum when scrolling past.
*   **Global Cursor Bug:** Re-coded the `useCursor` logic on [MoltenModel](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/components/canvas/Scene.tsx#101-154) meshes (which was turning the entire screen into a Hand tool) to strictly evaluate the `[interactive && hovered]` flag, restoring the default pointer globally.
*   **Hero & Alternating Row Overlaps:** Rectified the duplicated Hero components. Re-coded the [AlternatingRow](file:///C:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/src/app/page.tsx#56-72) section wrappers to deploy strict `lg:grid-cols-2` grids. Forcibly separated the Text Cards from the 3D Wrappers (`h-[400px]`), ensuring ZERO overlaps and restoring Awwwards proportion scaling.
*   **Mountain Spotlight & Footer Alignment:** Injected a 20x multiplier `spotLight` pointing precisely at [great_mountain.glb](file:///c:/Users/TUF/OneDrive/Desktop/Portfolio/public/great_mountain.glb) so its silhouette emerges from the void. Grounded the Footer Canvas securely inside the right column of the new Flex CTA grid to prevent bleeding past margins constraints.

